{
  "slug": "timezones-are-production-data",
  "title": "Timezones are production data",
  "category": "tech",
  "kicker": "Time is hard",
  "hook": "Time bugs are not caused by clocks being weird. They are caused by pretending human time is just a number.",
  "readMinutes": 5,
  "date": "2026-06-19",
  "tags": [
    "timezones",
    "systems"
  ],
  "beats": [
    {
      "num": "01 · the shape",
      "heading": "Midnight depends on where you stand",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "prose",
          "html": "<p class=\"body\">A subscription renews at midnight. Which midnight? The user, the business, the database, the server, or UTC? If nobody answers, production will.</p>"
        },
        {
          "type": "terminal",
          "title": "time · same instant",
          "caption": "The useful signal is usually already there.",
          "lines": [
            {
              "t": "2026-06-27T06:00:00Z",
              "c": ""
            },
            {
              "t": "America/Denver: 2026-06-27 00:00",
              "c": ""
            },
            {
              "t": "Europe/London: 2026-06-27 07:00",
              "c": ""
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "graph",
          "center": "request",
          "nodes": [
            "client",
            "edge",
            "API",
            "queue",
            "db",
            "cache"
          ],
          "caption": "Systems stories get more interesting when you can feel the pressure move through the stack.",
          "action": "add load",
          "idle": "system steady",
          "running": "pressure moving downstream...",
          "done": "6 infrastructure layers reacted"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "num": "02 · the move",
      "heading": "Store instants and intent",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "prose",
          "html": "<p class=\"body\">Use UTC for instants, but keep the user timezone or business timezone when the rule depends on local time.</p>"
        },
        {
          "type": "code",
          "file": "billing-schedule.json",
          "code": "{\n  \"renewAt\": \"2026-07-01T06:00:00Z\",\n  \"timezone\": \"America/Denver\",\n  \"rule\": \"local_midnight\"\n}",
          "caption": "The instant and the human rule are both part of the data."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "num": "03 · the check",
      "heading": "Test the ugly calendar days",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "prose",
          "html": "<p class=\"body\">Daylight saving changes, leap years, month ends, and travel can all break code that only tested a sunny Tuesday.</p>"
        },
        {
          "type": "lab",
          "title": "reliability control room",
          "caption": "Flip the switches and watch the story turn into a tiny operating model.",
          "toggles": [
            {
